ility or flexibility is a concern, a builder method like `with_txt_records` could still allow overrides.\n\n---\n\n## Finding 2: `rk_hex` computed twice (minor)\n\n**File:** `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/crates/reme-discovery/src/mdns_sd.rs`, lines 156-158\n\n`hex::encode(spec.routing_key)` is called once here for the instance name / FQDN. The same routing key is also hex-encoded inside the TXT records (via `encode_txt` at the call site). This is not a performance concern but reinforces Finding 1 -- the hex encoding of the routing key is done in two separate places with no guarantee of consistency.\n\n---\n\n## Non-findings (things that look fine)\n\n- **Removal of the `hostname` crate**: Clean. The `Cargo.toml` feature gate and the dependency line are both removed consistently.\n- **Test updates**: All test call sites pass distinct routing keys (`[0xAA; 16]`, `[0xBB; 16]`, etc.), which is good practice for test isolation.\n- **`AdvertisementSpec::new` signature change**: Adding `routing_key` as a required parameter is the right call -- it enforces that every advertisement carries identity information. The doc comment is updated to match.\n- **Comment update in `start_advertising`**: Correctly reflects the removal of the hostname lookup step.\n\n---\n\n## Verdict\n\nThe branch is solid. The only actionable item is Finding 1: consider having `AdvertisementSpec` own the TXT record generation for the routing key field to eliminate the data duplication and consistency risk between `spec.routing_key` and `spec.txt_records[\"rk\"]`. This would also simplify the call site in `apps/client/src/discovery/mod.rs`. Everything else is clean.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>38222</total_tokens><tool_uses>7</tool_uses><duration_ms>38432</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-reme/6dcb51e7-6371-44a9-bc5f-f368fca884ac/tasks/af03680dcf2febe21.output",
