            "content": "# Node Graceful Shutdown\n\n**Issue:** #128 — node cleanup task has no graceful shutdown\n**Date:** 2026-03-26\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\nThe standalone node (`apps/node`) has no signal handling. On SIGTERM/SIGINT the process dies immediately — no WAL checkpoint, no in-flight request draining, no cleanup of future stateful subsystems (mDNS, relay queue). Background tasks (cleanup, MQTT subscriber) are fire-and-forget `tokio::spawn` with no cancellation path.\n\n## Design\n\n### Signal handling\n\nA `shutdown_signal()` async function listens for SIGINT (`ctrl_c`) and SIGTERM (unix only). When either fires, it cancels a shared `CancellationToken`.\n\n```rust\nasync fn shutdown_signal(cancel: CancellationToken) {\n    let ctrl_c = tokio::signal::ctrl_c();\n    #[cfg(unix)]\n    let mut sigterm = tokio::signal::unix::signal(\n        tokio::signal::unix::SignalKind::terminate(),\n    ).expect(\"failed to install SIGTERM handler\");\n\n    tokio::select! {\n        _ = ctrl_c => info!(\"Received SIGINT, shutting down...\"),\n        #[cfg(unix)]\n        _ = sigterm.recv() => info!(\"Received SIGTERM, shutting down...\"),\n        _ = cancel.cancelled() => {},\n    }\n    cancel.cancel();\n}\n```\n\n### CancellationToken propagation\n\nA single `CancellationToken` is created at the top of `main()` and cloned into:\n\n1. **`shutdown_signal()`** — triggers cancellation on OS signal\n2. **`run_cleanup_task()`** — breaks the sleep/cleanup loop\n3. **MQTT subscriber** — exits its event loop\n4. **HTTP server** — stops accepting new connections and drains in-flight requests\n\n### Cleanup task changes\n\n`run_cleanup_task()` gains a `cancel: CancellationToken` parameter. The loop becomes:\n\n```rust\nloop {\n    tokio::select! {\n        _ = tokio::time::sleep(interval) => { /* cleanup */ }\n        _ = cancel.cancelled() => break,\n    }\n}\n// Final WAL checkpoint before exit\nstore.checkpoint().ok();\ninfo!(\"Cleanup task shut down\");\n```\n\n### MQTT subscriber\n\nThe spawned MQTT task receives the token. It exits its event loop when cancelled. The MQTT client disconnects on drop (existing behavior).\n\n### HTTP server shutdown\n\n**Plain HTTP mode:** `axum::serve(...).with_graceful_shutdown(cancel.cancelled_owned())`\n\n**TLS mode:** `axum_server` uses a `Handle` for shutdown control:\n```rust\nlet handle = axum_server::Handle::new();\n// In shutdown_signal, after cancel:\nhandle.graceful_shutdown(Some(Duration::from_secs(10)));\n```\n\n### Shutdown timeout\n\nA 10-second deadline after signal receipt. If in-flight requests don't drain, the process exits. Implemented via `tokio::time::timeout` wrapping the post-signal finalization, or via the `Handle` timeout for TLS mode.\n\n### Post-shutdown finalization\n\nAfter the HTTP server returns:\n1. Final WAL checkpoint (belt-and-suspenders — cleanup task also does one on exit)\n2. `info!(\"Node shut down cleanly\")`\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- Add `tokio-util = { workspace = true }` to `apps/node/Cargo.toml` (already in workspace for client)\n- Add `\"signal\"` to tokio features in `apps/node/Cargo.toml`\n\n## Files changed\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `apps/node/Cargo.toml` | Add `tokio-util`, add `signal` tokio feature |\n| `apps/node/src/main.rs` | Add `shutdown_signal()`, create token, wire into server and tasks |\n| `apps/node/src/cleanup.rs` | Add `CancellationToken` param, `select!` in loop, final checkpoint |\n\n## Not in scope\n\n- mDNS shutdown (separate PR, #145)\n- MQTT bridge graceful disconnect (the Rumqtt client disconnects on drop, sufficient for now)\n- Replication client shutdown (stateless HTTP client, no persistent connections to drain)\n\n## Success criteria\n\n- `cargo test` passes with no regressions\n- SIGINT/SIGTERM triggers clean shutdown with log message\n- WAL checkpoint runs on exit\n- Cleanup task stops promptly (no waiting for full sleep interval)\n- In-flight HTTP requests complete within 10s timeout\n",
