            "content": "# Node Graceful Shutdown — Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Add signal-based graceful shutdown to the standalone node so background tasks (cleanup, MQTT) stop cleanly, in-flight HTTP requests drain, and a final WAL checkpoint runs on exit.\n\n**Architecture:** A shared `CancellationToken` is created in `main()` and propagated to all background tasks and the HTTP server. A `shutdown_signal()` function listens for SIGINT/SIGTERM and cancels the token. Each background task uses `tokio::select!` to break its loop on cancellation.\n\n**Tech Stack:** tokio (signal feature), tokio-util (CancellationToken), axum (with_graceful_shutdown), axum-server (Handle for TLS mode)\n\n**Fixes:** #128\n\n---\n\n## File Map\n\n| File | Action | Responsibility |\n|------|--------|---------------|\n| `apps/node/Cargo.toml` | Modify | Add `tokio-util` dep, add `signal` tokio feature |\n| `apps/node/src/cleanup.rs` | Modify | Accept `CancellationToken`, use `select!` in loop, final checkpoint on exit |\n| `apps/node/src/main.rs` | Modify | Create token, add `shutdown_signal()`, wire token into tasks and server |\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Add dependencies\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/node/Cargo.toml`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add tokio-util and signal feature**\n\nIn `apps/node/Cargo.toml`, add `tokio-util` to dependencies and add `\"signal\"` to tokio features:\n\n```toml\n# async\nasync-trait = { workspace = true }\ntokio = { workspace = true, features = [\"rt-multi-thread\", \"macros\", \"sync\", \"time\", \"net\", \"signal\"] }\ntokio-util = { workspace = true }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Verify it compiles**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p node`\nExpected: compiles with no errors\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/node/Cargo.toml\ngit commit -m \"chore(node): add tokio-util and tokio signal feature for graceful shutdown\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Make cleanup task cancellable\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/node/src/cleanup.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write test for cancellable cleanup**\n\nAdd a test that verifies the cleanup task exits promptly when cancelled, rather than waiting for the full sleep interval. Add to the `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` block in `apps/node/src/cleanup.rs`:\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn test_cleanup_task_stops_on_cancel() {\n    use tokio_util::sync::CancellationToken;\n\n    let dir = tempfile::tempdir().unwrap();\n    let db_path = dir.path().join(\"test.db\");\n    let store_config = reme_node_core::PersistentStoreConfig {\n        max_messages_per_mailbox: 100,\n        default_ttl_secs: 3600,\n    };\n    let store =\n        Arc::new(reme_node_core::PersistentMailboxStore::open(db_path.to_str().unwrap(), store_config).unwrap());\n\n    let config = CleanupConfig {\n        enabled: true,\n        interval_secs: 3600, // 1 hour — task must NOT wait this long\n        ..CleanupConfig::default()\n    };\n\n    let cancel = CancellationToken::new();\n    let cancel_clone = cancel.clone();\n\n    let handle = tokio::spawn(async move {\n        run_cleanup_task(store, config, cancel_clone).await;\n    });\n\n    // Cancel immediately\n    cancel.cancel();\n\n    // Task should exit within 1 second, not wait for the 3600s interval\n    let result = tokio::time::timeout(Duration::from_secs(1), handle).await;\n    assert!(result.is_ok(), \"cleanup task did not stop promptly on cancel\");\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p node --lib cleanup::tests::test_cleanup_task_stops_on_cancel`\nExpected: FAIL — `run_cleanup_task` does not accept a `CancellationToken` parameter yet.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Update run_cleanup_task to accept CancellationToken**\n\nIn `apps/node/src/cleanup.rs`, add the import and modify the function signature and body:\n\nAdd to imports at the top of the file:\n```rust\nuse tokio_util::sync::CancellationToken;\n```\n\nReplace the `run_cleanup_task` function (lines 105–132) with:\n\n```rust\npub async fn run_cleanup_task(\n    store: Arc<PersistentMailboxStore>,\n    config: CleanupConfig,\n    cancel: CancellationToken,\n) {\n    if !config.enabled {\n        info!(\"Cleanup task disabled, exiting\");\n        return;\n    }\n\n    let interval = Duration::from_secs(config.interval_secs);\n    info!(\n        \"Starting cleanup task with {}s interval\",\n        config.interval_secs\n    );\n\n    loop {\n        tokio::select! {\n            () = tokio::time::sleep(interval) => {}\n            () = cancel.cancelled() => {\n                info!(\"Cleanup task received shutdown signal\");\n                break;\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Cleanup expired messages\n        match store.cleanup_expired() {\n            Ok(n) if n > 0 => info!(\"Cleaned {} expired messages\", n),\n            Ok(_) => debug!(\"Message cleanup: nothing to clean\"),\n            Err(e) => warn!(\"Message cleanup failed: {}\", e),\n        }\n\n        // Checkpoint WAL periodically\n        if let Err(e) = store.checkpoint() {\n            warn!(\"WAL checkpoint failed: {}\", e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Final WAL checkpoint before exit\n    if let Err(e) = store.checkpoint() {\n        warn!(\"Final WAL checkpoint failed: {}\", e);\n    } else {\n        info!(\"Final WAL checkpoint completed\");\n    }\n    info!(\"Cleanup task shut down\");\n}\n```\n\nAlso update the doc example above the function to reflect the new signature:\n\n```rust\n/// ```ignore\n/// let store = Arc::new(PersistentMailboxStore::open(\"mailbox.db\", config)?);\n/// let config = CleanupConfig::default();\n/// let cancel = CancellationToken::new();\n/// tokio::spawn(run_cleanup_task(store, config, cancel));\n/// ```\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p node --lib cleanup::tests::test_cleanup_task_stops_on_cancel`\nExpected: PASS\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run all node tests to verify no regressions**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p node --lib`\nExpected: all tests pass (existing tests don't call `run_cleanup_task` directly, only test `CleanupConfig`)\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/node/src/cleanup.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(node): make cleanup task cancellable via CancellationToken\n\nCloses #128\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Add shutdown_signal and wire graceful shutdown in main\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/node/src/main.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add shutdown_signal function**\n\nAdd these imports to the top of `apps/node/src/main.rs` (after existing `use` statements):\n\n```rust\nuse std::time::Duration;\nuse tokio_util::sync::CancellationToken;\n```\n\nAdd the `shutdown_signal` function after the existing `parse_log_level` function (after line 104):\n\n```rust\n/// Wait for SIGINT or SIGTERM, then cancel the shared token.\nasync fn shutdown_signal(cancel: CancellationToken) {\n    #[cfg(unix)]\n    let mut sigterm = tokio::signal::unix::signal(tokio::signal::unix::SignalKind::terminate())\n        .expect(\"failed to install SIGTERM handler\");\n\n    tokio::select! {\n        result = tokio::signal::ctrl_c() => {\n            if let Err(e) = result {\n                error!(\"Failed to listen for SIGINT: {}\", e);\n                return;\n            }\n            info!(\"Received SIGINT, shutting down...\");\n        }\n        #[cfg(unix)]\n        _ = sigterm.recv() => {\n            info!(\"Received SIGTERM, shutting down...\");\n        }\n        _ = cancel.cancelled() => {\n            // Already cancelled by another source\n            return;\n        }\n    }\n    cancel.cancel();\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Create CancellationToken in main and wire to cleanup task**\n\nIn `main()`, add the token creation right before the cleanup task spawn (before line 238 — the `// Spawn cleanup task` comment). Replace the cleanup task spawning block (lines 238–243):\n\nBefore (current):\n```rust\n    // Spawn cleanup task\n    let cleanup_store = Arc::clone(&store);\n    let cleanup_config = config.cleanup.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        run_cleanup_task(cleanup_store, cleanup_config).await;\n    });\n```\n\nAfter:\n```rust\n    // Create shared shutdown token\n    let cancel = CancellationToken::new();\n\n    // Spawn shutdown signal handler\n    tokio::spawn(shutdown_signal(cancel.clone()));\n\n    // Spawn cleanup task\n    let cleanup_store = Arc::clone(&store);\n    let cleanup_config = config.cleanup.clone();\n    let cleanup_cancel = cancel.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        run_cleanup_task(cleanup_store, cleanup_config, cleanup_cancel).await;\n    });\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Wire graceful shutdown to plain HTTP server**\n\nReplace the plain HTTP `axum::serve` block (lines 379–387):\n\nBefore (current):\n```rust\n        if let Err(e) = axum::serve(\n            listener,\n            app.into_make_service_with_connect_info::<SocketAddr>(),\n        )\n        .await\n        {\n            error!(\"Server failed: {}\", e);\n            std::process::exit(1);\n        }\n```\n\nAfter:\n```rust\n        if let Err(e) = axum::serve(\n            listener,\n            app.into_make_service_with_connect_info::<SocketAddr>(),\n        )\n        .with_graceful_shutdown(cancel.cancelled_owned())\n        .await\n        {\n            error!(\"Server failed: {}\", e);\n            std::process::exit(1);\n        }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Wire graceful shutdown to TLS server**\n\nReplace the TLS `axum_server::bind_rustls` block (lines 350–356):\n\nBefore (current):\n```rust\n        if let Err(e) = axum_server::bind_rustls(addr, rustls_config)\n            .serve(app.into_make_service_with_connect_info::<SocketAddr>())\n            .await\n        {\n            error!(\"Server failed: {}\", e);\n            std::process::exit(1);\n        }\n```\n\nAfter:\n```rust\n        let handle = axum_server::Handle::new();\n\n        // Spawn task to trigger graceful shutdown on cancel\n        let tls_handle = handle.clone();\n        let tls_cancel = cancel.clone();\n        tokio::spawn(async move {\n            tls_cancel.cancelled().await;\n            tls_handle.graceful_shutdown(Some(Duration::from_secs(10)));\n        });\n\n        if let Err(e) = axum_server::bind_rustls(addr, rustls_config)\n            .handle(handle)\n            .serve(app.into_make_service_with_connect_info::<SocketAddr>())\n            .await\n        {\n            error!(\"Server failed: {}\", e);\n            std::process::exit(1);\n        }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Add post-shutdown finalization**\n\nAt the end of `main()`, after the closing brace of the `if config.tls.enabled { ... } else { ... }` block (after the server returns), add:\n\n```rust\n\n    // Post-shutdown finalization\n    info!(\"HTTP server stopped, running final cleanup...\");\n    if let Err(e) = state.store.checkpoint() {\n        warn!(\"Final WAL checkpoint failed: {}\", e);\n    }\n    info!(\"Node shut down cleanly\");\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Verify it compiles**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p node`\nExpected: compiles with no errors\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Run all tests**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p node --lib`\nExpected: all tests pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Run workspace tests to verify no regressions**\n\nRun: `cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`\nExpected: all tests pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 9: Run clippy**\n\nRun: `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`\nExpected: no warnings\n\n- [ ] **Step 10: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/node/src/main.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(node): add graceful shutdown with signal handling\n\nWire CancellationToken through main() to all background tasks and\nthe HTTP/TLS server. SIGINT and SIGTERM trigger clean shutdown:\ndraining in-flight requests, stopping the cleanup task, and running\na final WAL checkpoint.\"\n```\n\n---\n